This paper discusses modern approaches in Information Extraction (IE) and its sub-tasks of Named Entity Recognition (NER) and Relation Extraction (RE). These tasks are closely related to natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning (ML), which are covered in the arXiv categories of cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions the recent trend towards deep learning (DL) based methods, which are covered in the arXiv categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper focuses on the specific task of Named Entity Recognition (NER), which is covered in the arXiv category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
